JOHANNESBURG The National Soccer League has appointed advocate Vincent Maleka to investigate the FNB Stadium stampede in which two people died.Maleka will be assisted by Mbana Incorporated.READ: Gauteng mourns two deaths at Soweto derbyThis comes after two soccer supporters died and others were injured during the Carling Black Label Champion Cup game between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs at at the FNB stadium on Saturday. Regarding the investigation, Mr Maleka SC is required to expeditiously prepare a report for the league in order for it to understand whether there has been proper attention to and compliance with the relevant laws, rules and regulations, governing, planning, management, and enforcement of safety and security measures at stadiums during football matches. "The league seeks to ensure that, to the extent possible, tragic incidents such as these are prevented whenever its member clubs are involved, the league said in a statement. eNCA